1
00:00:22,580 --> 00:00:27,660
♪Don't be afraid of the long journey♪

2
00:00:29,780 --> 00:00:34,740
♪Love will comfort your missing♪

3
00:00:34,900 --> 00:00:38,620
♪All the wounds will scab over♪

4
00:00:38,740 --> 00:00:41,980
♪And turn into the blossoms of time♪

5
00:00:41,980 --> 00:00:48,700
♪Someone will wipe them away for you♪

6
00:00:49,300 --> 00:00:52,580
♪Don't feel lonely, moving on♪

7
00:00:52,940 --> 00:00:56,420
♪Share your story with time♪

8
00:00:56,460 --> 00:01:03,100
♪It will respond
with a gentle beam of light♪

9
00:01:03,220 --> 00:01:06,820
♪Wishing you find her in the crowd♪

10
00:01:07,100 --> 00:01:10,220
♪And rest content with a simple life♪

11
00:01:10,380 --> 00:01:16,660
♪Even though life is full of regrets♪

12
00:01:17,380 --> 00:01:20,180
♪May you always maintain enthusiasm♪

13
00:01:20,220 --> 00:01:22,540
♪For every winter and summer♪

14
00:01:23,900 --> 00:01:25,980
[Love Is Panacea]
[Episode 21]

15
00:01:25,980 --> 00:01:26,960
[The show is the Major Project
for Supporting Literature and Art]

16
00:01:26,960 --> 00:01:27,980
[in Sichuan Province in 2022]

17
00:01:27,980 --> 00:01:29,980
[Based on the novel "Healer"
by Ningmeng Yuyan]

18
00:01:39,660 --> 00:01:41,660
Tonight, even if I work all night,

19
00:01:41,660 --> 00:01:42,700
I'll have to complete

20
00:01:42,700 --> 00:01:43,940
translating all the materials

21
00:01:44,060 --> 00:01:46,820
and make a clean break with you.

22
00:01:54,860 --> 00:01:57,060
Yuncheng? What are you doing here?

23
00:01:57,620 --> 00:01:58,620
You're working overtime.

24
00:01:58,860 --> 00:02:00,020
I guess you must be hungry.

25
00:02:00,020 --> 00:02:01,060
I brought you some food.

26
00:02:03,820 --> 00:02:04,700
Thank you, Yuncheng.

27
00:02:06,100 --> 00:02:07,020
Oh, fried chicken.

28
00:02:08,420 --> 00:02:09,580
Do you have to finish

29
00:02:09,700 --> 00:02:10,860
all these documents tonight?

30
00:02:11,100 --> 00:02:11,900
Yeah.

31
00:02:12,780 --> 00:02:15,340
The earlier I finish,
the sooner I get rid of Gu.

32
00:02:15,420 --> 00:02:17,260
Tonight, I must finish all this.

33
00:02:18,860 --> 00:02:19,780
Let me help you.

34
00:02:20,780 --> 00:02:21,580
No need.

35
00:02:22,060 --> 00:02:25,100
I can't bother you
with such a small part-time job.

36
00:02:25,100 --> 00:02:26,340
Oh, I see.

37
00:02:26,780 --> 00:02:28,500
You think I can't help you

38
00:02:28,500 --> 00:02:30,020
because I can't speak French, huh?

39
00:02:30,660 --> 00:02:32,260
Is it so easy to read my mind?

40
00:02:33,300 --> 00:02:34,780
I don't speak French,

41
00:02:34,780 --> 00:02:36,860
but I can help you revise the sheets,

42
00:02:36,860 --> 00:02:38,100
staple papers, or something.

43
00:02:38,100 --> 00:02:39,940
We'll be faster than you do it alone.

44
00:02:42,180 --> 00:02:43,020
Do you remember

45
00:02:43,580 --> 00:02:46,700
when we did the experiment all night?

46
00:02:46,860 --> 00:02:48,820
Speaking of which,
I quite miss the old days.

47
00:02:49,340 --> 00:02:50,700
Rather than saying you bother me,

48
00:02:50,700 --> 00:02:51,820
I would rather say

49
00:02:52,100 --> 00:02:54,780
you'll take me back to college days

50
00:02:54,780 --> 00:02:56,020
and make me feel young again.

51
00:02:59,260 --> 00:03:02,140
OK. Thank you, then.

52
00:03:03,380 --> 00:03:04,620
Don't stand on ceremony.

53
00:03:05,380 --> 00:03:07,580
Come on. Let's see

54
00:03:08,140 --> 00:03:09,540
if we can still work together

55
00:03:09,660 --> 00:03:12,340
as perfectly as we did before.

56
00:03:37,140 --> 00:03:39,140
This is what you asked me
to translate yesterday.

57
00:03:39,140 --> 00:03:40,660
I've translated it all. Please review.

58
00:03:50,060 --> 00:03:50,900
So soon?

59
00:03:51,940 --> 00:03:53,300
Are you sure you didn't do a poor job?

60
00:03:55,220 --> 00:03:56,740
Review as you wish.

61
00:03:58,180 --> 00:03:59,140
How's this possible?

62
00:03:59,140 --> 00:04:01,380
This isn't a task
you can finish in only one night.

63
00:04:03,020 --> 00:04:05,180
Last night, Yuncheng stayed up with me

64
00:04:05,180 --> 00:04:06,660
and helped me finish it.

65
00:04:07,620 --> 00:04:08,580
Du Yuncheng?

66
00:04:10,340 --> 00:04:12,380
You did the job with him?

67
00:04:14,100 --> 00:04:14,940
So, you two

68
00:04:15,820 --> 00:04:18,700
stayed in the lab all night?

69
00:04:18,820 --> 00:04:20,820
Yeah. Any problem?

70
00:04:23,340 --> 00:04:26,140
Su Wei'an, I got you back to the lab

71
00:04:26,700 --> 00:04:27,860
because I wanted you to work

72
00:04:28,100 --> 00:04:30,180
instead of dating in it.

73
00:04:30,580 --> 00:04:31,700
Who allowed you

74
00:04:31,700 --> 00:04:33,020
to take an outsider into my lab?

75
00:04:33,100 --> 00:04:34,780
Who was dating in the lab?

76
00:04:35,060 --> 00:04:36,140
Don't talk nonsense, OK?

77
00:04:38,620 --> 00:04:39,420
I said

78
00:04:39,820 --> 00:04:40,700
without my permission,

79
00:04:40,700 --> 00:04:42,820
no one is allowed into my lab.

80
00:04:42,820 --> 00:04:44,620
You chose not to listen, didn't you?

81
00:04:44,620 --> 00:04:45,260
Come on, man.

82
00:04:45,260 --> 00:04:46,540
Talk rationally, will you?

83
00:04:46,540 --> 00:04:48,260
I did translations for you,
but you cursed me.

84
00:04:49,900 --> 00:04:50,820
If Du Yuncheng was an outsider,

85
00:04:50,820 --> 00:04:51,900
I would also be one.

86
00:04:52,140 --> 00:04:53,580
If you're upset, scold someone else.

87
00:04:53,580 --> 00:04:54,580
Someone who upsets you.

88
00:04:54,700 --> 00:04:55,820
Why lose your temper with me?

89
00:04:58,300 --> 00:04:59,860
I'm not losing my temper with you.

90
00:04:59,940 --> 00:05:01,100
I don't care, though.

91
00:05:01,260 --> 00:05:03,340
Anyway, my translation work is done.

92
00:05:03,380 --> 00:05:04,500
Please review it now

93
00:05:04,500 --> 00:05:06,020
and give me the final payment.

94
00:05:06,180 --> 00:05:07,300
From this day on,

95
00:05:07,500 --> 00:05:08,860
I don't need to work here.

96
00:05:08,860 --> 00:05:10,100
Nor do I need

97
00:05:10,660 --> 00:05:12,020
to be squeezed by you anymore.

98
00:05:29,100 --> 00:05:32,020
No work in the lab tonight?

99
00:05:32,540 --> 00:05:34,580
Yesterday, I worked all night there.

100
00:05:34,940 --> 00:05:36,580
Want me to die from overwork?

101
00:05:37,020 --> 00:05:38,140
Just asking.

102
00:05:38,380 --> 00:05:40,860
What? Are you angry?

103
00:05:40,860 --> 00:05:41,700
Having your period?

104
00:05:41,700 --> 00:05:44,100
I think Gu Yunzheng is having a period.

105
00:05:51,760 --> 00:05:53,620
[Gu Yunzheng: ￥80000.00, final payment]

106
00:05:53,620 --> 00:05:54,700
So much money?

107
00:05:57,040 --> 00:05:58,600
[The translations
have been reviewed. Clear.]

108
00:06:02,300 --> 00:06:03,620
I think he can have his period

109
00:06:04,100 --> 00:06:05,020
more often.

110
00:06:11,540 --> 00:06:12,340
Miss Su.

111
00:06:12,940 --> 00:06:13,780
An?

112
00:06:14,300 --> 00:06:15,100
What a surprise!

113
00:06:17,340 --> 00:06:18,340
You... You two...

114
00:06:18,500 --> 00:06:20,020
This is my boyfriend.

115
00:06:20,260 --> 00:06:21,620
My only boyfriend.

116
00:06:29,140 --> 00:06:31,140
He is your only boyfriend.

117
00:06:31,300 --> 00:06:32,420
What about Gu Yunzheng?

118
00:06:33,340 --> 00:06:34,180
Dr. Gu...

119
00:06:35,340 --> 00:06:36,620
He isn't even an ex-boyfriend.

120
00:06:36,660 --> 00:06:39,620
He's just a man I failed to get.

121
00:06:42,860 --> 00:06:45,140
So, Dr. Gu turned you down?

122
00:06:45,180 --> 00:06:47,020
Yeah. He really did.

123
00:06:47,020 --> 00:06:48,540
He's kind of the first failure

124
00:06:48,540 --> 00:06:50,140
I've ever met in my life.

125
00:06:50,580 --> 00:06:52,820
Sweetheart, you're gorgeous.

126
00:06:55,180 --> 00:06:56,080
We should go, then.

127
00:07:08,020 --> 00:07:09,100
What's all this about?

128
00:07:11,100 --> 00:07:12,380
So, Gu Yunzheng

129
00:07:12,940 --> 00:07:14,380
didn't have anyone else.

130
00:07:14,820 --> 00:07:16,780
He's been caring about you.

131
00:07:18,420 --> 00:07:20,340
Then, has he been acting?

132
00:07:21,460 --> 00:07:22,740
But why would he?

133
00:07:24,180 --> 00:07:26,100
A medical diet restaurant
was opened near the hospital.

134
00:07:26,100 --> 00:07:28,020
I just took my girlfriend there,

135
00:07:28,260 --> 00:07:29,380
and I brought back some.

136
00:07:29,900 --> 00:07:31,530
Would you like to try some soup?

137
00:07:32,140 --> 00:07:34,180
Are you sure this is leftover food?

138
00:07:36,140 --> 00:07:37,020
(Miss Su,)

139
00:07:37,100 --> 00:07:38,500
(please open it and taste some.)

140
00:07:38,620 --> 00:07:39,780
(If it tastes good, tell me.)

141
00:07:39,780 --> 00:07:41,050
(I want to give it to my girlfriend.)

142
00:07:41,180 --> 00:07:43,620
(Dr. Gu, I'm your translator)

143
00:07:43,620 --> 00:07:44,860
(rather than a lab rat.)

144
00:07:47,620 --> 00:07:48,380
(I'll pay you more.)

145
00:07:49,800 --> 00:07:51,200
[The translations
have been reviewed. Clear.]

146
00:07:52,340 --> 00:07:54,180
He deliberately gave me more money

147
00:07:54,540 --> 00:07:55,580
in case I didn't take it.

148
00:07:57,940 --> 00:07:58,780
Oh, my tummy hurts.

149
00:08:00,940 --> 00:08:01,780
Jiang...

150
00:08:03,660 --> 00:08:04,940
Jiang Muying.

151
00:08:13,580 --> 00:08:15,620
You're familiar with this surgery, huh?

152
00:08:20,620 --> 00:08:21,900
You're done with the surgery, Boss.

153
00:08:23,380 --> 00:08:25,140
Why did you choose this approach?

154
00:08:26,580 --> 00:08:27,380
Any problem?

155
00:08:27,900 --> 00:08:29,100
I still have time to change it.

156
00:08:29,100 --> 00:08:29,820
I'm asking

157
00:08:29,820 --> 00:08:30,660
why you choose an approach

158
00:08:30,660 --> 00:08:32,380
that is seldom used

159
00:08:32,620 --> 00:08:35,020
instead of the most reliable
pterional approach.

160
00:08:35,500 --> 00:08:37,140
That girl is only 17 years old.

161
00:08:38,420 --> 00:08:40,540
She told me she loved
singing and dancing.

162
00:08:40,900 --> 00:08:42,300
And she wants
to major in performing arts.

163
00:08:42,860 --> 00:08:44,260
Her tumor isn't very big.

164
00:08:44,540 --> 00:08:46,500
To protect her hearing
and facial nerves,

165
00:08:46,820 --> 00:08:48,580
I chose the approach
with the smallest cut.

166
00:08:50,300 --> 00:08:51,100
The smallest cut

167
00:08:51,620 --> 00:08:52,860
leads to the smallest surgical field.

168
00:08:53,140 --> 00:08:54,580
You need complicated operations.

169
00:08:55,340 --> 00:08:58,860
In this case, I'll keep peeling it

170
00:08:59,620 --> 00:09:00,620
until it's all gone.

171
00:09:01,260 --> 00:09:02,100
Aren't you scared?

172
00:09:05,380 --> 00:09:06,100
I am.

173
00:09:07,140 --> 00:09:08,620
But Su Wei'an reminded me.

174
00:09:10,180 --> 00:09:11,380
She said

175
00:09:11,380 --> 00:09:12,660
when a doctor gives the surgery,

176
00:09:12,660 --> 00:09:13,620
he must attentively focus.

177
00:09:14,100 --> 00:09:15,380
As he holds the scalpels,

178
00:09:15,380 --> 00:09:16,900
he must give the best treatment.

179
00:09:18,380 --> 00:09:19,940
Su Wei'an said that?

180
00:09:20,100 --> 00:09:20,860
Mm.

181
00:09:22,100 --> 00:09:23,620
That day, Dr. Li also told me

182
00:09:23,820 --> 00:09:25,620
to pick the most secure approach

183
00:09:25,860 --> 00:09:27,620
to break my mental barriers.

184
00:09:28,260 --> 00:09:29,900
But I agree with Su Wei'an, actually.

185
00:09:31,340 --> 00:09:32,340
She's awesome.

186
00:09:32,620 --> 00:09:33,700
If she hadn't dropped out,

187
00:09:34,060 --> 00:09:35,860
she would be a very great doctor.

188
00:09:37,180 --> 00:09:38,260
She will come back.

189
00:09:46,620 --> 00:09:47,540
What, Boss?

190
00:09:52,860 --> 00:09:53,860
She didn't accept that money?

191
00:09:54,820 --> 00:09:56,260
That's not Su Wei'an's style.

192
00:10:01,660 --> 00:10:02,500
Oh, no, Boss.

193
00:10:02,940 --> 00:10:04,540
Jiang said she gave away the secret.

194
00:10:04,580 --> 00:10:06,020
She said Su Wei'an had known

195
00:10:06,420 --> 00:10:08,020
you lied to her about your girlfriend.

196
00:10:22,820 --> 00:10:23,620
Wei'an.

197
00:10:25,140 --> 00:10:27,180
You're going to work in the hospital?

198
00:10:30,580 --> 00:10:32,380
If the new medicine
doesn't come on the market,

199
00:10:33,820 --> 00:10:36,100
what are you going to do?

200
00:10:37,380 --> 00:10:38,140
Aunt Yuan,

201
00:10:38,140 --> 00:10:40,300
it's not what I should worry about.

202
00:10:41,180 --> 00:10:43,060
Why is it not?

203
00:10:45,340 --> 00:10:47,580
You also have the disease-causing genes.

204
00:10:51,860 --> 00:10:54,860
That report can only
deceive your mother.

205
00:10:57,300 --> 00:10:58,540
I can't hide anything from you.

206
00:10:59,860 --> 00:11:01,020
I can see

207
00:11:01,660 --> 00:11:04,900
you and Dr. Gu like each other.

208
00:11:05,140 --> 00:11:06,020
That's not true.

209
00:11:08,860 --> 00:11:10,020
Like my mother said,

210
00:11:10,860 --> 00:11:12,380
Dr. Gu is excellent,

211
00:11:12,420 --> 00:11:13,580
and I'm not good enough for him.

212
00:11:19,820 --> 00:11:20,700
I think

213
00:11:21,820 --> 00:11:22,820
since the drugs' withdrawal,

214
00:11:24,180 --> 00:11:26,180
I've been doing worse.

215
00:11:28,620 --> 00:11:31,060
In many cases,
I can't control my emotions.

216
00:11:32,260 --> 00:11:34,380
I feel I'm not what I used to be.

217
00:11:38,660 --> 00:11:40,940
I don't want you to be like me.

218
00:11:42,820 --> 00:11:43,620
I want you

219
00:11:43,620 --> 00:11:45,620
to be braver than me

220
00:11:47,140 --> 00:11:48,300
and have no regrets.

221
00:11:51,620 --> 00:11:52,380
Aunt Yuan,

222
00:11:53,900 --> 00:11:55,140
I'm doing great now.

223
00:11:55,580 --> 00:11:56,780
I have no regrets.

224
00:11:58,340 --> 00:12:00,020
As long as our family stick together

225
00:12:00,580 --> 00:12:01,940
and always live a happy life,

226
00:12:02,420 --> 00:12:03,620
that'd be enough for me.

227
00:12:45,540 --> 00:12:48,320
[Dos and Don'ts]

228
00:12:55,020 --> 00:12:56,540
(The handwriting...)

229
00:12:57,260 --> 00:12:58,540
(It's Gu Yunzheng.)

230
00:13:11,620 --> 00:13:12,380
Mom.

231
00:13:13,580 --> 00:13:15,420
Where did you get this notebook?

232
00:13:16,860 --> 00:13:18,580
When I was in the hospital
for some medicine,

233
00:13:18,580 --> 00:13:19,860
Dr. Gu gave it to me.

234
00:13:20,580 --> 00:13:22,140
He's quite scrupulous.

235
00:13:22,140 --> 00:13:23,620
He wrote it personally, right?

236
00:13:28,900 --> 00:13:29,820
I'm going to bed.

237
00:13:30,260 --> 00:13:30,860
Sleep early, too.

238
00:13:30,860 --> 00:13:31,580
I will.

239
00:13:39,700 --> 00:13:41,020
(Look, Su Wei'an.)

240
00:13:41,940 --> 00:13:43,820
(You did extra data calculations for me)

241
00:13:44,100 --> 00:13:45,580
(and found many citations from papers.)

242
00:13:46,380 --> 00:13:48,300
(You've never stopped
your love for medicine.)

243
00:13:49,100 --> 00:13:50,620
(These habits of medical students...)

244
00:13:51,100 --> 00:13:53,340
(You keep them even
after four years away from school.)

245
00:13:54,620 --> 00:13:56,540
(Why do you always deny
what you really want?)

246
00:14:04,340 --> 00:14:07,740
[The translations
have been reviewed. Clear.]

247
00:14:08,860 --> 00:14:09,860
(You can keep refusing,)

248
00:14:10,540 --> 00:14:11,620
(but I won't give up.)

249
00:14:29,020 --> 00:14:31,060
Do you want so much
to distance yourself from me?

250
00:14:32,140 --> 00:14:33,700
You don't even eat
the biscuits I bought.

251
00:14:51,300 --> 00:14:52,420
Su Wei'an,

252
00:14:53,940 --> 00:14:54,860
you're really a...

253
00:14:57,860 --> 00:15:00,020
A childish lady
who always denies her feelings.

254
00:15:26,940 --> 00:15:28,420
♪Falling conversation♪

255
00:15:28,500 --> 00:15:31,060
♪Every word sounded innocent♪

256
00:15:34,660 --> 00:15:36,180
♪My eye fell♪

257
00:15:36,260 --> 00:15:38,820
♪On the lingering warmth of your palm♪

258
00:15:41,780 --> 00:15:43,820
♪Something I felt uneasy♪

259
00:15:44,220 --> 00:15:46,220
♪Nightmares disturbed me♪

260
00:15:49,500 --> 00:15:51,540
♪Forgive me for relying too much♪

261
00:15:51,940 --> 00:15:53,980
♪On first-aid hugs♪

262
00:15:56,780 --> 00:15:59,220
♪Your Secret♪

263
00:15:59,260 --> 00:16:03,020
♪Your sleep talk was heard by me♪

264
00:16:03,340 --> 00:16:06,140
♪I snickered and secretly put down♪

265
00:16:06,180 --> 00:16:10,540
♪All your wishes♪

266
00:16:13,060 --> 00:16:15,460
♪My Secret♪

267
00:16:15,540 --> 00:16:19,140
♪I no longer remember I was so alone♪

268
00:16:19,300 --> 00:16:21,460
♪I've longed that you would♪

269
00:16:21,580 --> 00:16:26,820
♪Still pluck at my coat-tail♪

270
00:16:26,940 --> 00:16:30,700
♪I'm loving you♪

271
00:16:46,280 --> 00:16:48,760
[White Rabbit Creamy Candy]

272
00:17:08,200 --> 00:17:09,320
Hello, Yuncheng.

273
00:17:09,640 --> 00:17:11,720
What's up so late?

274
00:17:12,720 --> 00:17:14,440
I just finished dinner with a client.

275
00:17:14,680 --> 00:17:16,600
Near your bar, coincidentally.

276
00:17:16,840 --> 00:17:18,120
I want to watch your performance.

277
00:17:18,800 --> 00:17:20,120
I didn't go to the bar today.

278
00:17:20,200 --> 00:17:21,160
I'm doing something else.

